6. (Optional) Create the reverse lookup zone for the AD domain.

If your AD domain does not already have a reverse lookup zone, you can create one for the applicable AD domain in your DNS.

a. On a Windows server from which you can configure your DNS, click the Start button and select Administrative Tools > Active Director Users and Computers. b. Under Roles in the tree view in the left panel of the Active Director Users and Computers window, expand DNS Server > DNS > ad-domain-name > Reverse Lookup Zones.

c. Right-click Reverse Lookup Zones and select New Zone from the drop-down menu.

The New Zone Wizard window opens.

d. In the New Zone Wizard window, click the Next button.

The Zone Type page appears.

